<p>This comprehensive list of CD player mechanisms at¬†<a href="http://www.dutchaudioclassics.nl/philips_cdm_cd_mechanism_list/">http://www.dutchaudioclassics.nl/philips_cdm_cd_mechanism_list/</a>¬†(<a href="/assets/images/2018/11/DutchAudioClassics.nl-Information-specifications-photos-and-service-manuals-of-Philips-Marantz-TDA1541-cd-players.pdf">local copy</a>) showed I needed a Philips CDM12.1 mechanism. This was easy to find on ebay as a ‚ÄúVAM1201 VAM1202 CDM12.1 CDM12.2 laser transport mechanism for Philips NEW‚Äù. Total cost with free shipping from Hong Kong was $13.</p>

<p>I also found this detailed guide¬†to replacing the laser mechanism <a href="https://www.hifigear.co.uk/blog/marantz-cd63se-laser-transport-mechanism-replacement/">https://www.hifigear.co.uk/blog/marantz-cd63se-laser-transport-mechanism-replacement/</a>¬†and the <a href="/assets/images/2018/11/Marantz-CD-67-SE-Service-Manual.pdf">Marantz-CD-67-SE-Service-Manual</a> (which wasn‚Äôt that helpful for this particular repair).</p>

